		<figcaption class="vf-figure__caption"></figcaption>
	</figure>
  <h4>PNG</h4>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Supports transparency.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Suitable for graphics and logos.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4>SVG</h4>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Ideal for icons, diagrams and illustrations.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Vector-based and extremely lightweight.</li>
  </ul>

	<figure class="vf-figure vf-figure--align vf-figure--align-centered">
		<img src="{{ '/images/content_images/LRO diagram 3.2.5b.avif' | url }}" alt="Use lazy loading for assets that are not required during the initial page render." loading="lazy">
		<figcaption class="vf-figure__caption"></figcaption>
	</figure>

  <h4>WebP</h4>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Modern format with better compression than JPEG and PNG.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Supported by most modern browsers.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4>AVIF</h4>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">New generation image format.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Provides extremely high compression.</li>
  </ul>

