    <li class="vf-list__item">Improved experience on slow networks</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Embedding Critical Images</h3>
  <p>Some images, such as logos or icons, are critical for page functionality.</p>
  <p>For very small images, embedding them directly into HTML can reduce network requests.</p>
  <p>Example</p>
  <pre class="vf-code-example__pre"><code>&lt;img src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAA..." alt="Logo"&gt;</code></pre>

  <p>Embedding allows the browser to display the image immediately when the HTML loads.
  This technique should only be used for very small images.</p>


  <h3>Media and Video Strategy</h3>

  <p>Videos are often much larger than images and can heavily impact performance.</p>

  <p>Best practices include:</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Avoid autoplay videos when possible</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Use thumbnail images instead of loading videos immediately</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Host videos on external platforms when appropriate</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Compress videos before embedding</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Load videos only when users interact with them</li>
  </ul>

  {# ── Accessibility Considerations ── #}
  <h2 id="accessibility" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Accessibility Considerations</h2>

  <p>Images and graphics can make content easier to follow and more welcoming, especially for people with cognitive or learning disabilities. They also help people with visual impairments orient themselves and understand the structure of a page.</p>

  <p>At the same time, images are a common source of accessibility barriers when they lack suitable text alternatives or when essential information is conveyed visually only.</p>

  <h3>Choosing an approach</h3>

  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Informative images:</strong> Summarise the key information the image adds.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Decorative images:</strong> Use a null alternative (alt="") when the image adds no meaningful information.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Functional images:</strong> Describe the action or destination (e.g., "Print", "Submit"), not the visual appearance.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Images of text:</strong> Avoid where possible (except logos); if used, include the same words in the alternative text.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Complex images (charts/diagrams):</strong> Provide a complete text equivalent of the data or message.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Groups of images:</strong> Provide one alternative text that covers the meaning of the set.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Image maps:</strong> Provide overall context plus meaningful alternative text for each clickable region.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Accessible Media</h3>

  <p>Audio and video can add significant value to scientific content, but they also introduce frequent accessibility barriers when key information is available only through sound or only through visuals.</p>

  <p>Plan for these barriers early through scripting, storyboarding, and recording, rather than trying to "fix" accessibility in post-production. A practical baseline is to ensure the content still makes sense if someone only hears it or only sees it.</p>

  <p>For audio quality, prioritise clear speech and reduce background noise or music so listeners can distinguish the speaker.</p>

  <p>For video, avoid visual patterns that can trigger seizures, make any overlay text readable with sufficient contrast and legible sizing, and ensure speaker visibility where possible.</p>

  {# ── Do / Don't ── #}
  <h2 id="dos-dont" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400 vf-search-client-side--no-index">Do / Don't</h2>

  <h3>Do</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Resize images before uploading</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Use modern formats such as WebP</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Use responsive images for different devices</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Lazy load non-critical images</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Compress images before deployment</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Use SVG for icons and diagrams</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Don't</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Upload images straight from cameras</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Use large hero images without optimisation</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Load decorative images that do not add value</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Use video backgrounds that autoplay</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Deliver large desktop images to mobile devices</li>
  </ul>

