  {# ── Metrics and Tools ── #}
  <h2 id="metrics" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Metrics and Tools</h2>

  <h3>Key metrics to monitor</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Image payload size</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Largest Contentful Paint</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Total page weight</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Number of image requests</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Recommended LRO benchmarks</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Individual image size ideally below 200–500 KB</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Total image payload ideally below 1 MB for content pages</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Critical images loaded within first render</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Image Optimisation Tools</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Image Resizer:</strong> Easily resize and compress your images without losing quality. Perfect for both individual and bulk image resizing.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Image Compressor:</strong> Reduce your image file sizes while keeping the original quality intact. Great for speeding up your site with minimal effort.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Squoosh:</strong> A handy tool that lets you compare your original and compressed images side-by-side. Supports formats like JPEG, PNG, and WebP.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Video Optimisation Tools</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Zamzar:</strong> A versatile tool for converting video formats quickly and easily. Perfect for making videos web-friendly.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Clideo:</strong> An easy online tool to compress video files without significantly affecting their quality. Perfect for quick optimisations.</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>VEED.IO:</strong> Compress and edit your videos online. Resize for different platforms or reduce file sizes to speed up your website.</li>
  </ul>

  {# ── Use Cases for Scientific Websites ── #}
  <h2 id="scientific-use-cases" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Use Cases for Scientific Websites</h2>

  <p>Scientific dataset pages often contain complex visualisations and images.</p>

  <p>Optimisation strategies include:</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Serving smaller preview images first</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Loading high-resolution figures only when users request them</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Using SVG diagrams instead of raster images</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Training and documentation pages benefit from smaller images and illustrations that prioritise readability and speed.</p>

